There is nothing unusual in making the lairs (cubilia) and caverns (antra) scoop out themselves (fodisse) the hollows into which the forces of nature have shaped the ground. Heinsius indeed accepted this <with spatiosa for spatioque) as right: So too Jacob and Munro, and lately Hildebrandt and Sudhaus.
